                            <comment id="12762680" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 6 Oct 2009 16:46:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;when enough compactions queued up, it would reject additional ones instead of waiting for a thread to free up.  this patch fixes that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763067" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 7 Oct 2009 14:16:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Chris Were reports on -user that this patch fixes the bug for him.  Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12763470" author="hudson" created="Thu, 8 Oct 2009 12:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #221 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/221/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/221/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    use CallerRunsPolicy instead of rejecting runnables on multi-threaded executors w/ blocking queues&lt;br/&gt;
patch by jbellis; tested by Chris Were for &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
